      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 79.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 79.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>和大怨，必有餘怨，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>When a reconciliation is effected (between two parties) after a great animosity, there is sure to be a grudge remaining (in the mind of the one who was wrong).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-079__align-002">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-079</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 79.2</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 79.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>安可以為善？是以聖人執左契，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>And how can this be beneficial (to the other)?</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-079__align-003">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-079</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 79.3</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 79.3</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>而不責於人。有德司契，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Therefore (to guard against this), the sage keeps the left-hand portion of the record of the engagement, and does not insist on the (speedy) fulfilment of it by the other party.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-079__align-004">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-079</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 79.4</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 79.4</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>無德司徹。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>(So), he who has the attributes (of the Dao) regards (only) the conditions of the engagement, while he who has not those attributes regards only the conditions favourable to himself.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
